        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 2 at 2:56PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 256 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Amarillo, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Amarillo.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 27 between mile markers 120 and 123.
Interstate 40 between mile markers 69 and 79.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
